What did you say? I can't hear you.

439
00:34:12,586 --> 00:34:14,850
- He said, ''No.''
- Amy.

440
00:34:14,921 --> 00:34:17,481
I said, ''No, sir.''

441
00:34:17,557 --> 00:34:21,721
You know, whenever we used
to call your folks in Chicago...

442
00:34:21,795 --> 00:34:23,922
I don't think there was
any trouble, was there?

443
00:34:28,902 --> 00:34:30,870
I don't know what
to make of it.

444
00:34:30,937 --> 00:34:35,897
-People are pointing your direction.
-What did they say?

445
00:34:35,976 --> 00:34:40,504
What I've been telling you
about the trouble and drugs.

446
00:34:40,580 --> 00:34:44,641
You seem to be having trouble since
you moved here. And I figured--

447
00:34:44,718 --> 00:34:47,346
You figured where there's smoke,
there's fire, right?

448
00:34:47,420 --> 00:34:49,388
Usually works like that.

449
00:34:50,390 --> 00:34:54,656
Look, you know I would never try
to take the place of your father.

450
00:34:54,728 --> 00:34:57,663
Well, there's no chance of that.

451
00:35:05,605 --> 00:35:07,869
Uh-oh, he's taking the car.

452
00:38:06,152 --> 00:38:07,983
Big time!

453
00:38:10,523 --> 00:38:12,582
What are you doing here?

454
00:38:12,659 --> 00:38:14,251
Watching.

455
00:38:14,327 --> 00:38:16,727
I thought I was alone.

456
00:38:16,796 --> 00:38:20,789
Not in this town.
There's eyes everywhere.

457
00:38:26,239 --> 00:38:29,606
- How come you don't like me?
