01:05:06,968 --> 01:05:08,458
Stupid?

733
01:05:08,537 --> 01:05:11,472
Think I don't see you looking at him
like some bitch in heat?

734
01:05:11,540 --> 01:05:13,474
You'll wrap those skinny legs
around anybody.

735
01:05:13,542 --> 01:05:14,600
Shut up!

736
01:05:16,311 --> 01:05:18,905
Is that what I get? Huh?

737
01:05:18,980 --> 01:05:20,811
I treated you decent!

738
01:05:22,450 --> 01:05:23,883
Shit.

739
01:05:35,630 --> 01:05:38,326
Put that down!
Don't even think about that.

740
01:05:38,400 --> 01:05:40,766
-Jesus!
- You think about it!

741
01:05:49,978 --> 01:05:52,037
Stop it, Chuck!

742
01:06:08,096 --> 01:06:10,530
'Bout through with you anyway.

743
01:06:23,912 --> 01:06:27,279
I'm sorry you have
to see me like this.

744
01:06:27,349 --> 01:06:30,512
I'll be okay. I'll sneak in
at home. I'll be fine.

745
01:06:30,585 --> 01:06:33,520
- Do I look okay?
- You'll pull through.

746
01:06:38,793 --> 01:06:41,057
Thanks for coming for me.

747
01:06:42,931 --> 01:06:44,865
I don't understand.

748
01:06:44,933 --> 01:06:47,367
There's nothing to understand.

749
01:06:47,435 --> 01:06:50,131
It's for taking on my father.

750
01:06:50,205 --> 01:06:54,107
Wait a minute.
I got no beef with him.

751
01:06:54,175 --> 01:06:58,407
No, wait. This is my fight, it's
with the town, not with one guy.

752
01:06:58,480 --> 01:07:02,849
You don't get to turn my fight
into a ''screw you'' to your old man.

753
01:07:12,494 --> 01:07:13,927
Hey, look...

754
01:07:16,798 --> 01:07:18,561
maybe--

755
01:07:21,102 --> 01:07:24,629
Maybe you shouldn't try so hard
to forget your brother...

756
01:07:26,441 --> 01:07:29,171
or to try to make your father
forget him, you know?

757
01:07:33,448 --> 01:07:36,281
- It's not that easy.
- I know.

758
01:07:38,453 --> 01:07:40,421
Do I still get the box?

759
01:07:41,323 --> 01:07:43,257
Gimme the box.

760
01:07:58,807 --> 01:08:00,240
Nice.

761
01:08:09,217 --> 01:08:11,151
Think you might ever kiss me?

762
01:08:57,165 --> 01:08:59,725
Harvey and Bernie
were here for a long time.

763
01:09:01,269 --> 01:09:03,203
They still talking
about that dance?

764
01:09:03,271 --> 01:09:04,704
Yeah.

765
01:09:09,310 --> 01:09:12,768
- What did you decide to do?
- It's not gonna happen.

766
01:09:14,849 --> 01:09:19,115
That's one more thing Ariel is not
going to forgive me for, but--

767
01:09:21,156 --> 01:09:25,092
Can you step out of the way enough
to realize she's doing this for you?

768
01:09:25,160 --> 01:09:26,593
Me?

769
01:09:28,263 --> 01:09:30,493
I don't see that.

770
01:09:30,565 --> 01:09:32,499
I just know that
when kids dance together...

771
01:09:32,567 --> 01:09:35,536
they become sexually irresponsible.

772
01:09:35,603 --> 01:09:37,662
I can't take the chance--

773
01:09:39,607 --> 01:09:41,541
What's so funny?

774
01:09:43,545 --> 01:09:47,242
You talk like that's the only thing
that gets them excited.

775
01:09:48,149 --> 01:09:51,880
Don't you remember when we used to
look at each other and get excited?

776
01:09:54,923 --> 01:09:56,857
It's just the same with them.

777
01:09:58,359 --> 01:10:00,486
You're not gonna put
their eyes out.

778
01:10:18,012 --> 01:10:20,810
None of this is gonna undo
one stupid accident.

779
01:10:22,250 --> 01:10:25,219
I'm responsible for
the spiritual life of this community.

780
01:10:27,555 --> 01:10:30,991
Shaw, you can't be
a father to everybody.

781
01:10:31,059 --> 01:10:33,050
You can't do that.

782
01:10:36,297 --> 01:10:38,731
I thought that at least
you believed in me.

783
01:10:50,712 --> 01:10:52,646
I never stopped.

784
01:10:55,517 --> 01:10:58,145
Be at the town council meeting
tomorrow night.

785
01:10:58,219 --> 01:10:59,652
Only fairies dance.

786
01:11:01,122 --> 01:11:03,056
I'll lay you flat, Ariel.

787
01:11:03,124 --> 01:11:06,753
Support Ren MacCormack at
the council meeting tomorrow night.

788
01:11:06,828 --> 01:11:08,853
You can make a difference!

789
01:11:08,930 --> 01:11:13,230
I'm calling to remind you
to come to the town council meeting.

790
01:11:17,906 --> 01:11:19,806
Hi.

791
01:11:19,874 --> 01:11:21,899
- Still hurt?
- Naw.

792
01:11:21,976 --> 01:11:23,944
Good.

793
01:11:24,012 --> 01:11:25,980
- Nervous?
- No. Uh-uh.

794
01:11:26,948 --> 01:11:28,381
Look, I--

795
01:11:29,651 --> 01:11:31,448
Yeah.

796
01:11:31,519 --> 01:11:33,453
Yeah, I'm nervous.

797
01:11:33,521 --> 01:11:36,979
I don't know what
I'm gonna say to the council.

798
01:11:37,058 --> 01:11:39,686
There's only seven of them, right?

799
01:11:41,329 --> 01:11:44,264
- Who else is gonna be there?
- Everybody.

800
01:11:45,667 --> 01:11:48,192
Take a deep breath.
You ready?

801
01:11:53,074 --> 01:11:56,305
What is it? The Holy Bible?

802
01:12:02,717 --> 01:12:04,708
Ah, this is great.

803
01:12:06,854 --> 01:12:09,322
This is great! What--

804
01:12:10,892 --> 01:12:13,292
How'd you know where
to find all this?

805
01:12:13,361 --> 01:12:14,794
Are you kidding?

806
01:12:20,335 --> 01:12:22,633
I wanna tell you something.

807
01:12:22,704 --> 01:12:24,137
Thanks.

808
01:12:34,415 --> 01:12:35,848
Come on.

809
01:12:42,557 --> 01:12:44,491
What the hell is that?

810
01:12:47,395 --> 01:12:49,761
- Oh, my God!
- Amy? What is it?

811
01:12:51,899 --> 01:12:54,094
''Burn in hell''?
This says, ''Burn in hell.''

812
01:12:56,537 --> 01:13:00,064
- Ren, what the hell is going on?
- Somebody's trying to make a point.

813
01:13:00,141 --> 01:13:01,699
Do you see now?

814
01:13:01,776 --> 01:13:04,768
You don't wave flags here
without people taking shots at them.

815
01:13:04,846 --> 01:13:06,871
This is not the first time.

816
01:13:06,948 --> 01:13:10,714
My business was off, but people
are taking business away from me.

817
01:13:10,785 --> 01:13:15,245
Your aunt's gotten ugly phone calls
and today your mother lost her job.

818
01:13:15,323 --> 01:13:16,756
Mom, is that true?

819
01:13:18,359 --> 01:13:20,384
Mr. Collins said
he heard things about you.

820
01:13:20,461 --> 01:13:22,520
He thought I ought to stay home
and be a proper mother.

821
01:13:22,597 --> 01:13:24,861
- What did you say?
- I told him to shove it.

822
01:13:24,932 --> 01:13:26,866
Damn it, Ethel, this is serious.

823
01:13:26,934 --> 01:13:28,799
- There's other jobs!
- Where?

824
01:13:28,870 --> 01:13:31,896
- Shouldn't you call the police?
- I don't know if it'll do any good.

825
01:13:31,973 --> 01:13:34,635
I'll get Jim Earlhaus over here.
Will you stop?

826
01:13:34,709 --> 01:13:37,041
Now will you stop?

827
01:13:38,346 --> 01:13:40,439
I don't understand this town.

828
01:13:40,515 --> 01:13:43,075
It's like something's
choking everybody...

829
01:13:43,151 --> 01:13:45,278
only they don't know
they're choking.

830
01:13:45,353 --> 01:13:46,501
Let me ask you something.
Why this dance in this town?

831
01:13:46,501 --> 01:13:48,765
Let me ask you something.
Why this dance in this town?

832
01:13:50,505 --> 01:13:54,100
It's not just about a dance.
Not anymore.

833
01:13:54,176 --> 01:13:56,337
I know.
That's what I mean.

834
01:13:57,312 --> 01:13:59,906
I watch you, I see.

835
01:14:06,588 --> 01:14:10,285
- You're not gonna understand this.
- Try me.

836
01:14:18,600 --> 01:14:22,434
When Dad first threatened to leave,
I thought it was because of me.

837
01:14:22,504 --> 01:14:27,874
I thought it was something
that I wasn't doing right.

838
01:14:28,910 --> 01:14:33,040
And I figured there was something
I could do to make it like it was...

839
01:14:33,115 --> 01:14:35,640
and then he'd want to stay,
you know.

840
01:14:38,153 --> 01:14:41,645
But when he left
just like that...

841
01:14:41,723 --> 01:14:46,353
I realized that everything I'd done
hoping that he'd stay--

842
01:14:48,263 --> 01:14:52,962
everything I'd done,
it didn't mean shit.

843
01:14:53,835 --> 01:14:55,268
Didn't matter.

844
01:14:57,406 --> 01:15:00,341
And I felt like,
''What difference does it make?''

845
01:15:02,711 --> 01:15:04,144
But now--

846
01:15:05,380 --> 01:15:09,077
Now I'm thinking...

847
01:15:09,151 --> 01:15:11,779
I could really do something,
you know.

848
01:15:13,422 --> 01:15:17,256
I could really do something
for me this time, you know...

849
01:15:19,327 --> 01:15:21,795
otherwise I'm just gonna disappear.

850
01:15:39,047 --> 01:15:43,313
All right, Virginia, that ends
the discussion on this issue.

851
01:15:43,385 --> 01:15:47,219
So the price of a dog license
will go from $3.50 to $4.50.

852
01:15:47,289 --> 01:15:50,349
A licensed pet is a happy one.

853
01:15:50,425 --> 01:15:53,121
That takes care of old business.
Burlington?

854
01:15:54,229 --> 01:15:57,392
Thank you, Virginia.
It was real good.

855
01:15:57,466 --> 01:16:02,199
Now we can consider
any new business.

856
01:16:03,839 --> 01:16:06,069
Excuse me.

857
01:16:06,141 --> 01:16:09,838
Before we begin, I want
to remind all you kids...

858
01:16:09,911 --> 01:16:13,403
we're conducting
an official meeting.

859
01:16:14,516 --> 01:16:17,246
We're not gonna tolerate
any disturbances.

860
01:16:20,088 --> 01:16:22,420
The floor is now open
for any new business.

861
01:16:22,491 --> 01:16:26,825
My name is Ren MacCormack and
I would like to move on behalf...

862
01:16:26,895 --> 01:16:31,389
of most of the senior class of
Bomont High School that the law...

863
01:16:31,466 --> 01:16:34,663
against public dancing within the
town limits of Bomont be abolished.

864
01:16:41,343 --> 01:16:44,005
Mr. Chairman,
could I address myself to this?

865
01:16:44,079 --> 01:16:45,706
You bet.

866
01:16:45,780 --> 01:16:49,045
Even if this was not a law...

867
01:16:49,117 --> 01:16:51,551
which it is...

868
01:16:51,620 --> 01:16:56,080
I'm afraid I would have difficulty
endorsing an enterprise...

869
01:16:56,158 --> 01:17:00,424
which is as fraught
with genuine peril...

870
01:17:00,495 --> 01:17:02,554
as I believe this one to be.

871
01:17:03,532 --> 01:17:09,368
Besides liquor and drugs, which
seem to accompany such an event...

872
01:17:09,437 --> 01:17:13,999
the thing that distresses me
even more, Ren...

873
01:17:14,075 --> 01:17:18,910
is the spiritual corruption
that can be involved.

874
01:17:18,980 --> 01:17:23,508
These dances and this kind of music
can be destructive.

875
01:17:23,585 --> 01:17:26,782
And, Ren, I'm afraid
you're gonna find...

876
01:17:26,855 --> 01:17:30,120
that most of the people in
our community will agree with me.

877
01:17:30,192 --> 01:17:31,659
I do.

878
01:17:34,563 --> 01:17:37,930
- That's all I have to say.
- A vote is in order on the motion.

879
01:17:37,999 --> 01:17:41,435
- Will all those opposed--
- Excuse me, I--

880
01:17:41,503 --> 01:17:44,836
- I would like to say something.
- Please sit down.

881
01:17:44,906 --> 01:17:46,931
This is outrageous!

882
01:17:47,008 --> 01:17:49,442
- If you think that we're--
- Eleanor, sit down.

883
01:17:54,583 --> 01:17:57,245
I think Mr. MacCormack
has a right to be heard.

884
01:18:04,960 --> 01:18:08,862
I just wanted to say a few words
about this motion...

885
01:18:08,930 --> 01:18:12,661
so that you wouldn't think
that we were...

886
01:18:12,734 --> 01:18:17,330
encouraging destruction
with this idea.

887
01:18:20,008 --> 01:18:24,035
''From the oldest of times, people
danced for a number of reasons.

888
01:18:25,113 --> 01:18:27,172
They danced in prayer...

889
01:18:27,249 --> 01:18:30,514
or so that their crops
would be plentiful...

890
01:18:30,585 --> 01:18:32,519
or so their hunt would be good.

891
01:18:33,855 --> 01:18:37,951
And they danced
to stay physically fit...

892
01:18:38,026 --> 01:18:41,587
and show their community spirit.

893
01:18:41,663 --> 01:18:44,496
And they danced to celebrate.''

894
01:18:47,402 --> 01:18:50,496
And that is the dancing
we're talking about.

895
01:18:51,573 --> 01:18:56,875
Aren't we told in Psalm 1 49?

896
01:18:59,614 --> 01:19:02,344
''Praise ye the Lord.

897
01:19:02,417 --> 01:19:05,545
Sing unto the Lord a new song.

898
01:19:07,522 --> 01:19:09,888
Let them praise his name
in the dance.''

899
01:19:09,958 --> 01:19:11,550
Amen.

900
01:19:12,827 --> 01:19:15,261
And it was King David--

901
01:19:15,330 --> 01:19:19,664
King David, who
we read about in Samuel.

902
01:19:19,734 --> 01:19:22,999
And what did David do?

903
01:19:23,071 --> 01:19:25,266
What did David do?
What did David do?

904
01:19:25,340 --> 01:19:31,176
''David danced before the Lord
with all his might...

905
01:19:31,246 --> 01:19:36,377
leaping and dancing
before the Lord.''

906
01:19:36,451 --> 01:19:39,011
Leaping and dancing.

907
01:19:46,494 --> 01:19:49,554
Ecclesiastes assures us...

908
01:19:51,766 --> 01:19:54,462
that there is a time
for every purpose under heaven.

909
01:19:57,172 --> 01:19:59,106
A time to laugh...

910
01:20:00,175 --> 01:20:02,109
and a time to weep.

911
01:20:03,878 --> 01:20:05,436
A time to mourn...

912
01:20:06,715 --> 01:20:10,048
and there is a time to dance.

913
01:20:21,296 --> 01:20:24,322
And there was a time for this law,
but not anymore.

914
01:20:24,399 --> 01:20:26,924
See, this is our time to dance.

915
01:20:27,001 --> 01:20:32,337
It is our way
of celebrating life.

916
01:20:34,676 --> 01:20:37,144
It's the way it was
in the beginning.

917
01:20:38,747 --> 01:20:43,912
It's the way it's always been.
It's the way it should be now.

918
01:21:03,605 --> 01:21:07,097
You know you were railroaded,
don't you? Huh?

919
01:21:08,343 --> 01:21:12,507
When are you gonna wake up
and smell the coffee?

920
01:21:12,580 --> 01:21:16,641
Shaw Moore walked into that meeting
with votes already in his pocket.

921
01:21:16,718 --> 01:21:19,516
- You didn't have a prayer.
- Bad pun, Andy.

922
01:21:22,023 --> 01:21:24,719
What are you gonna do now?

923
01:21:24,793 --> 01:21:26,226
It's over.

924
01:21:27,328 --> 01:21:29,296
What if it ain't?

925
01:21:29,364 --> 01:21:31,992
What if you have your dance
in Bayson?

926
01:21:32,066 --> 01:21:34,864
No. The whole point was
to do something here in Bomont.

927
01:21:34,936 --> 01:21:37,234
Bayson's, what,
thirty miles away?

928
01:21:39,107 --> 01:21:42,099
Not where it runs up
to these tracks it ain't.

929
01:21:45,013 --> 01:21:48,346
I figure if the Bomont fire trucks
can't cross these tracks...

930
01:21:48,416 --> 01:21:50,350
neither can the long arm
of the law.

931
01:21:50,418 --> 01:21:52,579
What about the long arm
of Reverend Moore?

932
01:21:52,654 --> 01:21:55,214
Remember he said if you could find
a way to convince him...

933
01:21:55,290 --> 01:21:57,554
it wouldn't be a spiritual
corruption, he'd think about it.

934
01:21:57,625 --> 01:22:00,651
- So?
- Make him think about it.

935
01:22:05,800 --> 01:22:09,759
''And I beheld and heard
an angel flying...

936
01:22:09,838 --> 01:22:13,171
through the midst of heaven
saying with a loud voice:

937
01:22:13,241 --> 01:22:16,699
'Woe, woe, woe...

938
01:22:16,778 --> 01:22:19,440
to the inhabiters of the earth.'

939
01:22:19,514 --> 01:22:24,747
And I saw a star fall
from heaven unto the earth...

940
01:22:24,819 --> 01:22:28,687
and the angel
was given the key...

941
01:22:28,756 --> 01:22:31,384
to the bottomless pit.

942
01:22:31,459 --> 01:22:35,862
And he opened
the bottomless pit...

943
01:22:35,930 --> 01:22:41,425
and there arose a smoke out of
the pit as smoke of a great furnace.

944
01:22:41,503 --> 01:22:46,497
And the sun and air were darkened
by reason of the smoke of the pit.''

945
01:22:48,543 --> 01:22:49,976
Yes?

946
01:22:50,044 --> 01:22:53,639
I used to get such a kick
watching you work up your sermons.

947
01:22:56,718 --> 01:23:00,245
- And now?
- It's different.

948
01:23:00,321 --> 01:23:05,953
I see the stage. I see costumes.
It's show business, isn't it?

949
01:23:08,396 --> 01:23:09,829
Well...

950
01:23:11,666 --> 01:23:16,228
it's the only way I know
to reach people's emotions.

951
01:23:20,375 --> 01:23:22,900
I haven't heard from you
for a while.

952
01:23:25,146 --> 01:23:27,171
When was it? Thursday?

953
01:23:28,583 --> 01:23:30,517
I was angry, you were angry.

954
01:23:32,186 --> 01:23:34,120
- I was not.
- Yes, you were.

955
01:23:36,558 --> 01:23:40,585
If you weren't, you would've
asked me what was wrong. You knew.

956
01:23:40,662 --> 01:23:44,792
Ariel, I cannot let
this dance happen.

957
01:23:44,866 --> 01:23:47,027
Ren MacCormack made
a lot of people stop and think.

958
01:23:47,101 --> 01:23:49,865
I object to that kind of music,
and I think you know why.

959
01:23:49,938 --> 01:23:52,668
- Because people fornicate to it.
- I never said that.

960
01:23:52,740 --> 01:23:55,641
- You told the church board that.
- That was not meant for your ears!

961
01:23:55,710 --> 01:23:58,338
When do my ears get old enough?
When do you stop protecting me?

962
01:23:58,413 --> 01:23:59,778
I'm no saint!

963
01:23:59,847 --> 01:24:02,179
It is my duty to look after
the spiritual growth of you--

964
01:24:02,250 --> 01:24:04,480
I'm not even a virgin.

965
01:24:07,021 --> 01:24:09,512
- Don't talk like that in here!
- Why not?

966
01:24:09,591 --> 01:24:14,051
Isn't this where I confess my sins
to my preacher? In church!

967
01:24:14,128 --> 01:24:18,121
I ask to be forgiven. Am I?
Oh, forgive me, deliver me!

968
01:24:18,199 --> 01:24:21,191
Don't do that in here. You
know better where to draw the line!

969
01:24:21,269 --> 01:24:23,703
Thank heavens you're here.
People are calling.

970
01:24:23,771 --> 01:24:26,331
They're over at the library.

971
01:24:30,712 --> 01:24:33,579
Roger! Eleanor!
What are you doing?

972
01:24:33,648 --> 01:24:35,582
We decided these books--

973
01:24:35,650 --> 01:24:39,416
Who's we? Whose authority
are you acting on?

974
01:24:39,487 --> 01:24:41,682
Hold it everybody!
Listen to me!

975
01:24:43,891 --> 01:24:47,054
When did you all decide
to sit in judgment?

976
01:24:48,930 --> 01:24:54,095
Who elected you to be the saviors
of everybody's souls in Bomont?

977
01:24:54,168 --> 01:24:57,467
We have a perfect right to determine
what our children--

978
01:24:59,974 --> 01:25:04,104
When you've burned all of these,
what are you gonna do then?

979
01:25:06,648 --> 01:25:08,582
Chris, take these out of here.

980
01:25:11,419 --> 01:25:14,616
Satan is not in these books.

981
01:25:14,689 --> 01:25:17,249
He's in here!

982
01:25:17,325 --> 01:25:20,158
He's in your hearts.

983
01:25:20,228 --> 01:25:22,856
Go on home, all of you.

984
01:25:22,930 --> 01:25:25,228
Go and sit in judgment
on yourselves.

985
01:25:27,135 --> 01:25:29,968
And, Roger, go home.

986
01:25:31,205 --> 01:25:32,695
Eleanor, come on.

987
01:25:34,776 --> 01:25:36,744
Go home now, both of you.

988
01:26:14,849 --> 01:26:17,147
Sometimes things
don't make any sense.

989
01:26:17,218 --> 01:26:21,621
If you could explain to me my father
maybe I could explain your son.

990
01:26:23,524 --> 01:26:25,458
But it doesn't make any sense.

991
01:26:29,230 --> 01:26:32,165
Look, I gotta go.

992
01:26:34,836 --> 01:26:37,862
Listen, I know you're gonna do
what you gotta do...

993
01:26:37,939 --> 01:26:41,773
but thanks for listening.

994
01:26:48,616 --> 01:26:50,641
Thank you for--

995
01:26:53,354 --> 01:26:56,551
Well, thank you.

996
01:27:11,873 --> 01:27:14,740
That was your friend Ren.

997
01:27:14,809 --> 01:27:18,575
He came here to ask me if he could
take you to a senior prom.

998
01:27:24,085 --> 01:27:26,076
I'm running out of answers.

999
01:27:28,122 --> 01:27:30,090
I know how hard it is for you.

1000
01:27:32,460 --> 01:27:34,928
I'm know I'm not making it easier.

1001
01:27:41,269 --> 01:27:45,137
I just don't know that I believe
in everything you believe in...

1002
01:27:48,409 --> 01:27:50,639
but I believe in you.

1003
01:28:15,269 --> 01:28:20,639
I'm standing up here
before you today...

1004
01:28:23,244 --> 01:28:25,508
with a very troubled heart.

1005
01:28:29,784 --> 01:28:30,989
You see, my friends...

1006
01:28:30,989 --> 01:28:31,921
You see, my friends...

1007
01:28:33,625 --> 01:28:36,890
I've always insisted on...

1008
01:28:36,962 --> 01:28:40,591
taking responsibility
for your lives.

1009
01:28:41,867 --> 01:28:45,030
But, I'm really...

1010
01:28:46,772 --> 01:28:49,434
like a first-time parent...

1011
01:28:50,509 --> 01:28:53,273
who makes mistakes...

1012
01:28:53,345 --> 01:28:56,712
and tries to learn from them.

1013
01:28:59,751 --> 01:29:02,242
And like that parent...

1014
01:29:03,555 --> 01:29:09,391
I find myself at that moment
when I have to decide.

1015
01:29:10,929 --> 01:29:12,863
Do I hold on...

1016
01:29:14,833 --> 01:29:19,099
or do I trust you
to yourselves?

1017
01:29:19,171 --> 01:29:24,666
Let go and hope
that you've understood...

1018
01:29:24,743 --> 01:29:28,440
at least some of my lessons.

1019
01:29:32,885 --> 01:29:36,844
If we don't start trusting
our children...

1020
01:29:36,922 --> 01:29:41,859
how will they
ever become trustworthy?

1021
01:29:44,696 --> 01:29:47,597
I'm told that the senior class
at the high school...

1022
01:29:47,666 --> 01:29:50,692
has got use of
the warehouse in Bayson...

1023
01:29:50,769 --> 01:29:55,468
for the purpose of
putting on a senior dance.

1024
01:29:56,909 --> 01:29:58,342
Please...

1025
01:30:00,012 --> 01:30:04,779
join me to pray
to the Lord...

1026
01:30:04,850 --> 01:30:06,841
to guide them
in their endeavors.

1027
01:31:45,217 --> 01:31:46,411
Lights!

1028
01:32:09,074 --> 01:32:11,042
- You look very nice.
- Oh, no.

1029
01:32:11,109 --> 01:32:13,873
Yes, you do.
Yes, you look very nice.

1030
01:32:13,945 --> 01:32:15,879
Yes, you do.
You look wonderful.

1031
01:32:15,947 --> 01:32:18,177
- You think?
- Yeah. Mm-hmm.

1032
01:32:23,689 --> 01:32:26,954
You can't very well go to a prom
without a corsage.

1033
01:32:29,795 --> 01:32:31,786
Oh, Mom.

1034
01:32:31,863 --> 01:32:33,888
This is gorgeous!

1035
01:32:38,670 --> 01:32:41,264
- Where do you think I should--
- Here's a wrist thing.

1036
01:32:41,339 --> 01:32:43,534
Oh, Mom, you really
didn't have to.

1037
01:32:43,608 --> 01:32:45,041
I didn't.

1038
01:32:48,814 --> 01:32:52,682
Don't go on to him about it
because he'll only deny it.

1039
01:33:04,563 --> 01:33:08,727
I was gonna come up and get--
I was...

1040
01:33:09,935 --> 01:33:12,495
gonna come up and get you.

1041
01:33:12,571 --> 01:33:16,632
- What's the matter?
- You're beautiful.

1042
01:33:20,212 --> 01:33:21,645
What?

1043
01:33:29,755 --> 01:33:34,249
I mean it.
You are beautiful.

1044
01:33:40,599 --> 01:33:42,032
Come on.

1045
01:33:53,011 --> 01:33:54,444
Thank you.

1046
01:36:04,476 --> 01:36:08,071
- Let's take a closer look.
- No. She'll think I'm checking up.

1047
01:36:08,146 --> 01:36:10,671
No. She won't even know
we're here. Come on.

1048
01:36:16,087 --> 01:36:18,920
You're the last folks I expected
to see around here tonight.

1049
01:36:18,990 --> 01:36:21,754
- Good evening, Andy.
- Hi, Andy.

1050
01:36:21,826 --> 01:36:23,953
Reverend, you done
a good thing here.

1051
01:36:24,963 --> 01:36:26,988
I'm still not sure
it was the right thing.

1052
01:36:27,065 --> 01:36:28,498
Comes close.

1053
01:36:46,518 --> 01:36:47,951
Shaw?

1054
01:36:58,697 --> 01:37:00,289
What is it?

1055
01:37:04,903 --> 01:37:07,303
It's just the two of us again.

1056
01:37:25,690 --> 01:37:28,124
- Shaw?
- What?

1057
01:37:29,728 --> 01:37:32,094
We're almost dancing.

1058
01:37:41,373 --> 01:37:43,841
- Hi, Rusty.
- Hi.

1059
01:37:54,085 --> 01:37:55,780
Hello, Willard.

1060
01:37:57,022 --> 01:37:58,956
You promised you won't fight.

1061
01:37:59,024 --> 01:38:00,889
Don't you look sweet.

1062
01:38:04,295 --> 01:38:08,254
- What do you want?
- I've got business with MacCormack.

1063
01:38:08,333 --> 01:38:10,927
Cool it, all right.
No fights tonight, okay?

1064
01:38:12,303 --> 01:38:14,237
Hey, no fights, fellas.

1065
01:38:15,440 --> 01:38:16,873
Sure, Willard.

1066
01:38:18,810 --> 01:38:20,675
All right.

1067
01:38:22,914 --> 01:38:25,781
Cute.
No fights, Willard.

1068
01:38:25,850 --> 01:38:30,514
Damn, man! I told you.
I promised Rusty no fights tonight.

1069
01:38:31,923 --> 01:38:34,289
Let me go, goddamn it!

1070
01:38:35,427 --> 01:38:38,225
- Oh, Willard!
- What do you want me to do, Rusty?

1071
01:38:38,296 --> 01:38:41,697
Kill the son of a bitch!
Help, somebody!

1072
01:38:44,936 --> 01:38:49,339
- Chuck!
- Hey, it's Mr. Dance Fever.

1073
01:38:49,407 --> 01:38:52,137
You're a goddamn hero
when it's five to one.

1074
01:38:54,112 --> 01:38:56,740
Ren, get up!
Beat the shit out of him!

1075
01:39:08,293 --> 01:39:09,783
Bastard!

1076
01:39:14,265 --> 01:39:16,028
You're gonna dance now.

1077
01:39:28,813 --> 01:39:30,246
All right!

1078
01:39:35,253 --> 01:39:37,414
- Hey, handsome.
- Great dance, man.

1079
01:39:37,489 --> 01:39:39,650
Fighter heroes!

1080
01:39:39,724 --> 01:39:42,750
I thought you guys were
actually gonna fight or something.

1081
01:39:42,827 --> 01:39:44,260
You're great.

1082
01:39:44,329 --> 01:39:48,288
Hey, what's this I see?
I thought this was a party.

1083
01:39:48,366 --> 01:39:49,993
Let's dance!

1084
01:40:11,589 --> 01:40:13,523
Just watch, all right?